      <li class="purple-3"><div class="key-label">Private companies</div><div class="key-percent">(5%)</div><br />like ProtonMail and ThinkPenguin</li>
    </ul>
  </figcaption>
</figure>

</div>

</div> 

<div class="row" id="expenses">

<div class="col-md-12">

<h3>How we spend our money</h3>



<figure class="chart">
  
  <div class="chart-content">
    <svg height="75%" viewbox="0 0 64 64" width="75%">
      
      <circle aria-labelledby="" cx="32" cy="32" fill="transparent" r="15.91549430918954" stroke="#7a478b" stroke-dasharray="38 62" stroke-dashoffset="25" stroke-width="32"></circle>
      <circle aria-labelledby="" cx="32" cy="32" fill="transparent" r="15.91549430918954" stroke="#9c6bad" stroke-dasharray="26 74" stroke-dashoffset="87" stroke-width="32"></circle>
      <circle aria-labelledby="" cx="32" cy="32" fill="transparent" r="15.91549430918954" stroke="#af97c7" stroke-dasharray="19 81" stroke-dashoffset="61" stroke-width="32"></circle>
      <circle aria-labelledby="" cx="32" cy="32" fill="transparent" r="15.91549430918954" stroke="#dadbdc" stroke-dasharray="17 83" stroke-dashoffset="42" stroke-width="32"></circle>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="chart-key">
    <ul class="chart-key-list">
      <li class="purple-1">
        <div class="key-label">Releases, maintenance, and infrastructure</div><div class="key-percent">(38%)</div>
        <p>Tails is an endless work of updates and maintenance: publishing a
        new release every 4 weeks to fix security vulnerabilities, adapting to
        new versions of the underlying software, keeping our website and
        development infrastructure secure and reliable, etc.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="purple-2">
        <div class="key-label">New features and major improvements</div><div class="key-percent">(26%)</div>
	<p>In 2022, we restructured the installation instructions, fixed many
        usability issues in the <i>Tor Connection</i> assistant, and redesigned
        the <i>Persistent Storage</i>.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="purple-3">
        <div class="key-label">User experience, documentation, and support</div><div class="key-percent">(19%)</div>
        <p>Even the most secure software is worthless if the people who need it
        cannot use it. We work hard to understand our users, make it easy to
        use Tails, and help them make informed security decisions.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="gray">
        <div class="key-label">Administration&nbsp;and fundraising</div><div class="key-percent">(17%)</div>
        <p>We make the most of the money that we receive because we prefer spending
        our time improving Tails for our users.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </figcaption>
</figure>

</div>

</div> 

<div class="row" id="recommended">

<div class="col-md-12">

<h3>Recommended by</h3>




<div class="testimonials">

<section class="quote">

<a href="https://twitter.com/Snowden/status/1165395796520554496"><img alt="Edward Snowden" class="img" height="200" src="./testimonials.inline/snowden.png" width="200" /></a>

<blockquote>
<a href="https://twitter.com/Snowden/status/1165395796520554496">
<p><em>If you look at the way post-2013 whistleblowers have been caught,
it is clear the absolute most important thing you can do to maintain
your anonymity is reduce the number of places in your operational
activity where you can make mistakes. Tor and Tails still do precisely
that.</em></p>
&mdash; <strong>Edward Snowden</strong>,<br />
NSA whistleblower
</a>
</blockquote>

</section>

<section class="quote">

<a href="https://www.torproject.org/"><img alt="Tor Project" class="img" height="200" src="./testimonials.inline/tor.png" width="200" /></a>

<blockquote>
<p><em>Tails expands Tor&#39;s protections to an entire operating system, and
they do so with an unwavering commitment to their Social Contract. Tails
is a favorite companion tool of Tor.</em></p>
&mdash; <strong>Roger Dingledine</strong>,<br />
co-founder of the Tor Project
</blockquote>

</section>

<section class="quote">

<a href="https://www.eff.org/"><img alt="EFF" class="img" height="200" src="./testimonials.inline/eff.png" width="200" /></a>

<blockquote>
<a href="https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2014/10/7-privacy-tools-essential-making-citizenfour">
<p><em>One of the most robust ways of using the Tor network is through a
dedicated operating system that enforces strong privacy- and
security-protective defaults. That operating system is Tails.</em></p>
&mdash; <strong>EFF</strong>,<br />
Electronic Frontier Foundation
</a>
</blockquote>

</section>

<section class="logos">

<a href="https://accessnow.org/"><img alt="Access Now" class="img" height="70" src="./testimonials.inline/accessnow.png" width="200" /></a>

<a href="https://riseup.net/"><img alt="Riseup" class="img" height="100" src="./testimonials.inline/riseup.png" width="200" /></a>

</section>

